    definition: "Container modification refers to altering a shipping container for purposes beyond basic storage. Common modifications include adding doors, windows, insulation, electrical wiring, HVAC systems, and interior finishing. Modified containers are used for offices, workshops, retail spaces, tiny homes, and more. In Saskatchewan, modified containers are popular for remote work sites and agricultural applications.",
    slug: "container-modification"
  }
];

